"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-sport-boxing-1929570-Olympic-boxing-Imane-Khelif-Lin-Yu-Ting\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"  Two female boxers who were ejected from last year's Women's World Boxing Championships after being deemed biologically male will be allowed to compete at theOlympics.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 168, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 68, \"end\": 74, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"score\": 0.999999999524789, \"rank\": 4.751070893070828e-10, \"text\": \"Boxing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Imane Khelif of Algeria and Lin Yu-Ting of Taiwan were found to have XY chromosomes, which determine a person's biological sex as male.The discovery resulted in both boxers being disqualified from last year's World Championships by the International Boxing Association.\", \"from\": 169, \"to\": 438, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 169, \"end\": 181, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"score\": 0.9999996421621021, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Imane Khelif\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Imane_Khelif\"}, {\"begin\": 185, \"end\": 192, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.9999987718941422, \"rank\": 1.0478380520632856e-06, \"text\": \"Algeria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}, {\"begin\": 197, \"end\": 208, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lin Yu-Ting\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lin_Yu-ting\"}, {\"begin\": 212, \"end\": 218, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.9999659492254357, \"rank\": 1.254612287007437e-05, \"text\": \"Taiwan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}, {\"begin\": 238, \"end\": 252, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"XY chromosomes\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/XY_sex-determination_system\"}, {\"begin\": 405, \"end\": 437, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.60101332145185e-30, \"text\": \"International Boxing Association\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Women's_International_Boxing_Association\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The governing body made the controversial decision to conduct DNA tests at the event, which was held in India in March last year.In spite of the IBA's ruling, the two boxers will be allowed to compete at the Olympics after being cleared by the International Olympic Committee.\", \"from\": 439, \"to\": 715, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 543, \"end\": 548, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"score\": 0.9482117752538828, \"rank\": 0.051351501806180415, \"text\": \"India\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/India\"}, {\"begin\": 584, \"end\": 587, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.6689520852225209, \"rank\": 0.4948746046089054, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}, {\"begin\": 683, \"end\": 714, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The IBA does not have jurisdiction over Olympic boxing, with the IOC taking control without having robust eligibility guidelines on the matter.\", \"from\": 716, \"to\": 859, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 720, \"end\": 723, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.6689520852225209, \"rank\": 0.4948746046089054, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}, {\"begin\": 781, \"end\": 784, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0850830846528895e-27, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Pick up your ultimate guide to the Olympics!\", \"from\": 861, \"to\": 905, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Going for Gold provides the day-by-day rundown of what's on and when.\", \"from\": 906, \"to\": 975, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Clickhereto buy.\", \"from\": 976, \"to\": 992, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Discovery+is the new home of the Olympics.\", \"from\": 996, \"to\": 1038, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The streamer is set to broadcast 3,800 hours of sport live from Paris.\", \"from\": 1039, \"to\": 1109, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1103, \"end\": 1108, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999976116669, \"rank\": 2.388436020978321e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sports fans can getDiscovery+ for \\u00a33.99a month until the end of 2024 via Amazon Prime's video channels.\", \"from\": 1111, \"to\": 1214, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1184, \"end\": 1196, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amazon_Prime\", \"score\": 0.9975781888196168, \"rank\": 0.0024276904326192526, \"text\": \"Amazon Prime\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amazon_Prime\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amazon_Prime\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This also comes with anAmazon Prime 30-day free trial.\", \"from\": 1215, \"to\": 1269, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"An IOC statement released on Monday read: \\\"All athletes participating in the boxing tournament of the Olympic Games Paris 2024 comply with the competition's eligibility and entry regulations, as well as all applicable medical regulations, in accordance with rules 1.4 and 3.1 of the Paris 2024 Boxing Unit.\", \"from\": 1271, \"to\": 1577, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1274, \"end\": 1277, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0850830846528895e-27, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1565, \"end\": 1571, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"score\": 0.999999999524789, \"rank\": 4.751070893070828e-10, \"text\": \"Boxing\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boxing\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The decision to allow Khelif and Lin to compete at the Olympics is likely to be controversial, with former world champion Barry McGuigan among those to have commented on social media.\", \"from\": 1577, \"to\": 1761, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1700, \"end\": 1705, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barry_Gibb\", \"score\": 0.99871287213429, \"rank\": 0.0012887861742453914, \"text\": \"Barry\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barry_Gibb\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Barry_Gibb\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Taking to X, formerly Twitter, he wrote: \\\"It's shocking that they were actually allowed to get this far.\", \"from\": 1762, \"to\": 1866, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"What is going on?\", \"from\": 1867, \"to\": 1884, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"IBA president Umar Kremlev said last year that DNA test results exposed 'athletes who were trying to fool their colleagues and pretend to be women'.\", \"from\": 1884, \"to\": 2033, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1885, \"end\": 1888, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.6689520852225209, \"rank\": 0.4948746046089054, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}, {\"begin\": 1899, \"end\": 1903, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Umar\", \"score\": 0.9999999495366877, \"rank\": 5.015631225833642e-08, \"text\": \"Umar\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Umar\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Umar\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He confirmed that multiple boxers had been disqualified in the interests of 'fairness among athletes and professionalism'.\", \"from\": 2034, \"to\": 2156, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Do not miss:Show your colours and get Team GB's official kit for the Paris Olympics  Do not miss:Olympic gymnast cries in pain as she forces body to continue with torn ligament  Do not miss:Princess Anne presents Team GB's first Gold Medal as she makes subtle tribute  Khelif was removed from her gold medal bout, with Janjaem Suwannapheng allowed to progress despite losing to the Algerian boxer in the semi-finals.\", \"from\": 2158, \"to\": 2574, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2196, \"end\": 2203, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9998779938637693, \"rank\": 0.00011905731878242804, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 2540, \"end\": 2548, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.9997676848925833, \"rank\": 0.0001988624775566526, \"text\": \"Algerian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, the Algerian Olympic Committee disputed the IBA ruling and accused the governing body of conspiring against it.Brianda Tamara, a Mexican boxer who fought Khelif at last year's World Championships, described her punching power in a post on social media.She wrote: \\\"When I fought with her I felt very out of my depth.\", \"from\": 2575, \"to\": 2899, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2588, \"end\": 2614, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algerian_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Algerian Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algerian_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algerian_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 2628, \"end\": 2631, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"score\": 0.6689520852225209, \"rank\": 0.4948746046089054, \"text\": \"IBA\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Independent_Broadcasting_Authority\"}, {\"begin\": 2703, \"end\": 2709, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tamara_Todevska\", \"score\": 0.9854711581825343, \"rank\": 0.014742809234714611, \"text\": \"Tamara\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tamara_Todevska\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tamara_Todevska\"}, {\"begin\": 2713, \"end\": 2720, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexicans\", \"score\": 0.9233142012197669, \"rank\": 0.0823204832125081, \"text\": \"Mexican\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mexicans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Her blows hurt me a lot.\", \"from\": 2900, \"to\": 2924, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I do not think I had ever felt like that in my 13 years as a boxer, nor in my sparring with men.\", \"from\": 2925, \"to\": 3021, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Thank God that day I got out of the ring safely, and it's good that they finally realised.\", \"from\": 3022, \"to\": 3112, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Khelif and Lin are due to begin their Olympic campaigns later this week, with the former competing in the welterweight division and the latter in the featherweight category.\", \"from\": 3112, \"to\": 3286, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"SEARCH  CONNECT WITH US  TODAY'S PAPER  See today's front and back pages, download the newspaper, order back issues and use the historic Daily Express newspaper archive.\", \"from\": 3288, \"to\": 3457, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3425, \"end\": 3438, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.221109932587402e-17, \"text\": \"Daily Express\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Daily_Express\"